{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ce34f805-30d2-4e80-800a-8ea9a5612296","content":"Here's the clarification for .NET MAUI on .NET 10:\n\n**`ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\"`** — ✅ This is correct. It's the iOS platform-specific attached property that keeps your page content within the safe area (away from the notch/Dynamic Island). You'll need the namespace:\n\n```xml\nxmlns:ios=\"clr-namespace:Microsoft.Maui.Controls.PlatformConfiguration.iOSSpecific;assembly=Microsoft.Maui.Controls\"\n```\n\n**`IgnoreSafeArea=\"True\"` on a Grid** — ❌ This property does **not exist** in .NET MAUI. Your tutorial is likely outdated or incorrect.\n\nTo have a background image extend behind the safe area while keeping content safe, use a layered approach:\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns:ios=\"...\"\n             ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"False\">\n    <Grid>\n        <!-- Background fills entire screen including unsafe area -->\n        <Image Source=\"bg.png\" Aspect=\"AspectFill\" />\n        <!-- Content respects safe area via padding -->\n        <Grid Padding=\"{OnPlatform iOS='44,0,34,0'}\">\n            <!-- Your content here -->\n        </Grid>\n    </Grid>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\nAlternatively, keep `UseSafeArea=\"True\"` on the page and place the background image in a parent layout that uses negative margins or an absolute layout to bleed outside the safe area.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"04168f19-4e0b-4932-a573-d4b7482d4882","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about .NET MAUI safe area handling on iOS, specifically about two properties:\n1. `ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\"` on ContentPage\n2. `IgnoreSafeArea=\"True\"` on a Grid\n\nLet me search for any relevant documentation or code in the current repository that might help answer this question about .NET MAUI safe area APIs on .NET 10.\n\nActually, looking at the environment, this is a repository with skill plugins. Let me check if there's any relevant .NET MAUI content here. But actually, the user is asking a general knowledge question about .NET MAUI APIs. Let me answer based on my knowledge.\n \nSo `ios:Page.UseSafeArea` is the platform-specific property from the iOSSpecific namespace that controls safe area behavior on iOS, while `IgnoreSafeArea` on a Grid appears to be a more recent or alternative approach in .NET MAUI for handling safe area insets at the control level rather than the page level. I'm realizing that `IgnoreSafeArea` isn't actually a standard property in .NET MAUI either. The proper way to handle safe areas is through `ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\"` on the page level, but there's no direct property on Grid to ignore safe areas for specific elements. So `IgnoreSafeArea` isn't actually a valid property in .NET MAUI—the tutorial might be outdated or mixing in Xamarin.Forms concepts. The correct approach for .NET 10 is still using `Page.UseSafeArea` to control safe area behavior, and I should clarify this distinction for the user.","outputTokens":1347,"requestId":"0810:187D22:AC036D:C793CC:69F2AB99"},"id":"3dcd27cb-5051-4b0b-b4d5-278a318f9e11","timestamp":"2026-04-30T01:09:07.202Z","parentId":"3edf912a-4fd7-4040-aac9-302b2579eb98"}
